  {
    "content": "What is the minimum number of 2-input NOR gates required to implement a 4-variable function function expressed in sum-of-minterms form as \n<br><br>f = Σ(0, 2, 5, 7, 8, 10, 13, 15)? \n<br><br>Assume that all the inputs and their complements are available.",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "3",
    "explanation": "<p>Given : 4-variable SOP form is, $f=\\Sigma m(0,2,5,7,8,10,13,15) \\rightarrow$ SOP form</p>\n<p>Here, examines asked about implementation of function using NOR gate only so it is better to solve function $(f)$ in POS form.</p>\n<p>So, POS form function $(f)$ is, \n\n<br><br>$f=\\pi M(1,3,4,6,9,11,12,14) \\rightarrow$ POS form Now, making K-map in POS format for function $(f)$ is,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m49fvdml/08df826c-88e3-428e-af39-3f85097dd059/6481cde0-b1ff-11ef-a4cf-d34aad14607c/file-jaoe38c1m49fvdmm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m49fvdml/08df826c-88e3-428e-af39-3f85097dd059/6481cde0-b1ff-11ef-a4cf-d34aad14607c/file-jaoe38c1m49fvdmm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CSE 2019 Digital Logic - K Maps Question 5 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Minimized form of $f$ in POS format is, </p>\n<p>$f=(\\bar{b}+d)(b+\\bar{d}) \\rightarrow$ EX-NOR in POS form </p>\n<p>So, 2-input EX-NOR gate using 2-input NOR gate is shown below,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m49fyh0w/07edc049-3673-421e-9a8d-442245685f8c/ba8eeb00-b1ff-11ef-a4cf-d34aad14607c/file-jaoe38c1m49fyh0x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m49fyh0w/07edc049-3673-421e-9a8d-442245685f8c/ba8eeb00-b1ff-11ef-a4cf-d34aad14607c/file-jaoe38c1m49fyh0x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CSE 2019 Digital Logic - K Maps Question 5 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>Hence , minimum number of 2 - input NOR gate required is 3 . </p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2019,
    "yearKey": "gate-cse-2019",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "content": "Consider the minterm list form of a Boolean function 𝐹 given below. $$F\\left( {P,Q,R,S} \\right) = $$ $$\\sum {m\\left( {0,2,5,7,9,11} \\right)} $$ $$ + \\,\\,d\\left( {3,8,10,12,14} \\right)$$ \n<p>Here, $$m$$ denotes a minterm and $$d$$ denotes a don’t care term. The number of essential prime implicants of the function $$F$$ is ___________.</p>\n",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "3",
    "explanation": "<p><strong>Solution Explanation</strong></p>\n<p>We are given a 4‐variable Boolean function</p>\n<p>$ F(P, Q, R, S) \\;=\\; \\sum m(0, 2, 5, 7, 9, 11) \\;+\\; d(3, 8, 10, 12, 14), $</p>\n<p>where</p>\n<p></p><p>$m(\\dots)$ are the minterms where $F=1,$</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>$d(\\dots)$ are the “don’t‐care” terms, which may be treated as either 0 or 1 during simplification.</p><p></p>\n<hr>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m597ye7g/d1b96f9d-69c4-49a1-93f5-c685c3e60df9/a6ba2ac0-c5ac-11ef-a4e2-fb8e7cf702cd/file-jaoe38c1m597ye7h.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m597ye7g/d1b96f9d-69c4-49a1-93f5-c685c3e60df9/a6ba2ac0-c5ac-11ef-a4e2-fb8e7cf702cd/file-jaoe38c1m597ye7h.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CSE 2018 Digital Logic - K Maps Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>So, number of Essential Prime Implicant (EPI) $=\\mathbf{3}$</p>",
